---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { site, waLink } from '../data/site';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="About Our UK IPTV Trial Service"
  description="The story behind IPTV Trial — why we built a genuine 30-day IPTV trial for UK viewers tired of dodgy providers, hidden charges and disappearing support."
  eyebrow="Our Story"
  heading="Built by viewers who got burned, for viewers who won't be."
  intro="IPTV Trial started with a simple frustration: too many providers take your money, ghost your messages, and leave you stuck with a service that buffers through every match. This is the story of why we built something different — and why we'll always let you try it before you commit."
  updated="July 2026"
  noIndex={false}
  includeSchema={true}
>
  <h2>1. Why we exist</h2>
  <p>
    Before {site.name} existed, we were customers just like you. We paid for “premium” IPTV subscriptions from providers who promised the world on their websites and delivered almost nothing once the money hit their account. Streams froze during penalty shootouts. Channels vanished mid-season. Support agents answered once and then disappeared for weeks. And when we asked for refunds? Silence.
  </p>
  <p>
    We heard the same story from friends, family and, eventually, from our own community of viewers. The pattern was always the same — a slick landing page, an aggressive lifetime deal, a WhatsApp reply for the first 24 hours, and then a ghost town. That is the reality of the IPTV market in the UK today, and it is why so many people are (rightly) sceptical the moment the words <em>IPTV subscription</em> appear on a screen.
  </p>
  <p>
    {site.name} was built to be the opposite of that experience. Not because we wrote a clever slogan, but because we lived the bad version first and refused to build another one.
  </p>

  <h2>2. What our customers told us — and what we changed</h2>
  <p>
    When we started onboarding early users, we did something most providers never do: we asked them to describe their <strong>worst</strong> IPTV experience. The answers were painfully consistent, and they became the blueprint for how we operate today.
  </p>

  <h3>“They took my money and vanished.”</h3>
  <p>
    This was the number one complaint. A one-year package sold for £70, credentials that worked for two weeks, and then a dead line. Our answer: we don't lead with lifetime or yearly deals. We lead with a <strong>30-day IPTV trial for {site.currencySymbol}{site.price}</strong> so you never have to hand over a large amount up front to a provider you have not tested.
  </p>

  <h3>“Support ignored me the moment something broke.”</h3>
  <p>
    Every provider claims “24/7 support.” Most of them mean “an auto-reply and a prayer.” We use a real WhatsApp line answered by real UK-hours humans, and we treat trial customers exactly the same as long-term subscribers. If you cannot get a reply, you cannot trust the service — full stop.
  </p>

  <h3>“It buffered every time I actually wanted to watch.”</h3>
  <p>
    Buffering is not bad luck, it is bad infrastructure. Cheap providers cram thousands of users onto oversold servers and shrug when the Premier League kicks off. We invest in dedicated UK and EU servers with anti-buffer routing, and we scale capacity <em>before</em> match nights, not after complaints roll in.
  </p>

  <h3>“The channel list on the website did not match what I got.”</h3>
  <p>
    Padded channel counts are the oldest trick in the IPTV playbook. What we advertise is what you get access to on your first day — live UK sports, movies, series, kids, news, international channels, and a genuine on-demand library. If a channel goes down, we say so; we do not pretend it was never there.
  </p>

  <h3>“I could not cancel or get a refund.”</h3>
  <p>
    We published a clear <a href="/refund">refund policy</a> and we honour it. If our service is not working for you, we would rather send your money back than trap you into a contract you resent. Trust compounds; forced renewals do not.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Why we lead with a trial, not a lifetime deal</h2>
  <p>
    The IPTV industry has trained UK viewers to expect one of two things: an unrealistic “lifetime” offer that quietly dies six months in, or a heavy annual up-front payment to a company you have never met. Both put all the risk on you, the customer. If the service turns out to be poor, you have already paid — and getting anything back is a fight.
  </p>
  <p>
    A trial flips that risk. For {site.currencySymbol}{site.price}, you get a real 30-day IPTV subscription with the full lineup, the full server quality, and the full support experience. You test us against your actual usage — your Smart TV, your Fire Stick, your broadband, your favourite matches — and <em>only then</em> do you decide whether to continue. If we are not what we say we are, you have lost the price of a takeaway, not the price of a holiday.
  </p>
  <p>
    We are confident enough in the service to structure it this way. Any provider that refuses to let you try before you commit is telling you something about how well their service holds up under real conditions.
  </p>

  <h2>4. What we actually deliver</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>50,000+ live channels</strong> — UK, Irish, US, European, MENA and international sports, entertainment, news, kids and documentaries.</li>
    <li><strong>On-demand library</strong> — thousands of movies and full TV series in 4K UHD, FHD and HD.</li>
    <li><strong>Anti-buffer UK &amp; EU servers</strong> with 99.9% uptime and dedicated capacity for match nights.</li>
    <li><strong>Any device</strong> — Smart TVs, Fire Stick, Android, iOS, Windows, Mac, MAG, Formuler, Nvidia Shield, Apple TV and Enigma2.</li>
    <li><strong>Real UK-hours support</strong> — reachable by WhatsApp and email, answered by humans who know the product.</li>
    <li><strong>No auto-renewals, no hidden tiers, no upsells.</strong> One clean price, one clean service.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. How we handle trust</h2>
  <p>
    Trust in this industry is not earned with copywriting, it is earned by doing the boring things well for a long time. That means:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Answering messages when the football is on, not just when it is quiet.</li>
    <li>Being honest when something is temporarily down and explaining what we are doing about it.</li>
    <li>Refunding without an argument when we said we would.</li>
    <li>Keeping our pricing the same for you as it was on the day you signed up.</li>
    <li>Never selling, sharing or trading your personal data — see our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for the full detail.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We would rather grow slowly with customers who stay for years than fast with customers who feel tricked after a week.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Who we are for</h2>
  <p>
    {site.name} is for UK households who are tired of overpaying for traditional cable and satellite packages, tired of being burned by shady IPTV resellers, and tired of committing to services they have not been allowed to test. If you want to watch what you actually want to watch — live sport, films, box sets, international channels — on the devices you already own, without paying £70+ a month or gambling on a stranger, you are exactly who we built this for.
  </p>
  <p>
    We are not for people looking for the cheapest possible reseller with no support. There are dozens of those, and they will disappoint you within weeks. We are the boring, reliable, answers-the-phone version — and the {site.trialDays}-day trial exists so you can prove that to yourself before you commit to anything longer.
  </p>

  <h2 id="team">7. Who writes for us</h2>
  <p>
    Our content is written and fact-checked by <strong>James Whitfield</strong>, an IPTV consultant based in the UK with five years' experience testing streaming infrastructure for broadcasters and independent providers. James writes the buying guides, legal explainers, setup walkthroughs and app reviews on this site — every article is tested against a live IPTV subscription before it is published.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Where to go next</h2>
  <p>
    If any of this sounds like the experience you have been looking for, the fastest way to test us is to start the {site.currencySymbol}{site.price} trial and put us on your own TV tonight. If it is not for you, our <a href="/refund">refund policy</a> is there for a reason. If you would rather talk to a human first, message us on <a href={waLink()} target="_blank" rel="noopener">WhatsApp</a> or email <a href={`mailto:${site.supportEmail}`}>{site.supportEmail}</a> and we will answer — properly.
  </p>
  <p>
    Thank you for reading this far. Most people who do end up trying the service, and most who try it stick around. If you still have questions before committing, message us on WhatsApp or send an email. We will answer properly.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-top:2rem;">
    <a href="/#pricing" class="btn-primary" style="text-decoration:none;">Start the {site.currencySymbol}{site.price} 30-day trial</a>
  </p>
</LegalLayout>

<style is:global>
  /* About page: use full-contrast white body text for readability on mobile. */
  main .legal-prose p,
  main .legal-prose li,
  main .legal-prose h3 {
    color: #F5F7FA !important;
  }
</style>
